.TH "devm_clk_register" 9 "devm_clk_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_clk_register \- resource managed clk_register()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct clk *" devm_clk_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct clk_hw *hw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that is registering this clock
.IP "hw" 12
link to hardware-specific clock data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed \fBclk_register\fP. This function is *deprecated*, use \fBdevm_clk_hw_register\fP instead.

Clocks returned from this function are automatically \fBclk_unregister\fPed on
driver detach. See \fBclk_register\fP for more information.
